        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 22 at 5:01PM PDT by NWS Hanford CA</headline>
        <description>At 501 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 12
miles southwest of Big Pine Creek Campground, or 12 miles south of
South Lake, moving north at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail and brief heavy
rain.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
State Lakes, Monarch Ranger Station, Simpson Meadow Patrol Cabin,
Blackcap Basin, Le Conte Canyon Ranger Station, Bishop Pass, and
McClure Meadow Ranger Station.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
